00:15:42.325 --> 00:15:44.527
you're seen as not needing anything.

256
00:15:46.446 --> 00:15:47.780
you're basically ignored.

257
00:15:51.576 --> 00:15:53.161
Like. no one comes looking for you.

258
00:15:57.039 --> 00:15:58.040
But you did.

259
00:15:59.542 --> 00:16:01.294
So I just wanted to say thank you.

260
00:16:04.630 --> 00:16:05.965
I'll always come looking for you.

261
00:16:21.189 --> 00:16:22.273
Would you stay with me?

262
00:16:25.401 --> 00:16:26.402
Okay.

263
00:16:49.550 --> 00:16:50.843
I don't want to die here.

264
00:16:56.516 --> 00:16:57.683
I'll keep you safe.

265
00:16:59.977 --> 00:17:00.978
I promise.

266
00:17:11.822 --> 00:17:14.200
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

267
00:17:18.496 --> 00:17:20.706
When was the last time you slept?

268
00:17:20.707 --> 00:17:22.208
I'm used to long shifts.

269
00:17:23.793 --> 00:17:24.794
Go grab some sleep.

270
00:17:28.589 --> 00:17:29.882
I need you at full strength.

271
00:17:33.427 --> 00:17:35.513
[WHEEZING AND GROANING]

272
00:17:39.100 --> 00:17:40.101
That girl...

273
00:17:42.228 --> 00:17:43.437
Did you guys kill her?

274
00:17:46.983 --> 00:17:48.276
Maybe it was an accident...

275
00:17:49.402 --> 00:17:51.112
but maybe it was something
more than that.

276
00:17:52.655 --> 00:17:54.156
You're asking me if I'm a killer?

277
00:17:57.076 --> 00:17:58.077
Or Dawn?

278
00:18:01.747 --> 00:18:02.957
And we're going around...

279
00:18:04.917 --> 00:18:07.878
killing your friends. our friends?

280
00:18:07.879 --> 00:18:08.963
Someone has been.

281
00:18:11.382 --> 00:18:13.300
Peter...

282
00:18:13.301 --> 00:18:14.343
did you kill her?

283
00:18:17.138 --> 00:18:18.139
Peter.

284
00:18:19.515 --> 00:18:21.726
Hey. hey. I'm right
here. I'm right here.

285
00:18:23.561 --> 00:18:24.604
Blame me.

286
00:18:27.064 --> 00:18:27.898
What?

287
00:18:30.151 --> 00:18:31.986
When you get out...

288
00:18:35.114 --> 00:18:37.950
just tell the police it was me.

289
00:18:47.043 --> 00:18:49.045
- Talvinder...
- Stop. stop.

290
00:18:54.175 --> 00:18:55.509
I assaulted her.

291
00:19:05.811 --> 00:19:07.146
It's all on me.

292
00:19:17.823 --> 00:19:19.033
It's all on me.

293
00:19:33.214 --> 00:19:34.215
Is that true?

294
00:19:38.302 --> 00:19:40.388
[LABORED BREATHING]

295
00:19:57.738 --> 00:19:59.615
[NO AUDIO]

296
00:20:11.127 --> 00:20:13.587
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [YELLING AND SCREAMING]

297
00:20:13.588 --> 00:20:16.590
You said you would keep me safe.

298
00:20:16.591 --> 00:20:17.925
I'm sorry.

299
00:20:18.509 --> 00:20:19.719
You promised.

300
00:20:21.220 --> 00:20:22.388
[GASPS]

301
00:20:25.266 --> 00:20:27.435
[PANTING]

302
00:20:32.440 --> 00:20:34.400
- I'll be right back.
- Okay.

303
00:20:44.994 --> 00:20:47.204
[NOAH. WHEEZING BREATHS]

304
00:20:50.458 --> 00:20:52.543
[LABORED BREATHING. GROANS]

305
00:21:02.386 --> 00:21:05.138
[MUFFLED GROANING]

306
00:21:05.139 --> 00:21:06.724
One of us here is a killer.

307
00:21:12.521 --> 00:21:13.814
We all know it's true.

308
00:21:17.777 --> 00:21:19.403
Keira. can you come join
us in here. please?

309
00:21:22.990 --> 00:21:23.824
What is it?

310
00:21:25.326 --> 00:21:26.576
Noah needs me right now.

311
00:21:26.577 --> 00:21:28.412
Just sit for a minute. please.

312
00:21:34.668 --> 00:21:37.087
What most of you already
know about me is that...

313
00:21:37.088 --> 00:21:39.089
in a previous life. I was an attorney.

314
00:21:41.383 --> 00:21:44.428
What you don't know.
what I didn't tell you.

315
00:21:46.013 --> 00:21:49.350
is that I was paid very. very well...

316
00:21:50.851 --> 00:21:52.895
to be a tough son of a bitch.

317
00:21:53.562 --> 00:21:55.105
I loved the game of it.

318
00:21:55.106 --> 00:21:59.109
I kind of got off on it because
I was really. really good.

319
00:22:00.110 --> 00:22:02.708
And I'm not gonna sit around here

320
00:22:02.709 --> 00:22:05.740
waiting. doing nothing until rescue.

321
00:22:05.741 --> 00:22:08.536
I need to use my skills...

322
00:22:10.120 --> 00:22:12.081
and question each and every one of you.

323
00:22:13.874 --> 00:22:16.459
until I can suss out
exactly who the killer is.

324
00:22:16.460 --> 00:22:19.004
I'm sorry. Are you playing
lawyer or judge here?

325
00:22:19.005 --> 00:22:21.464
Yeah. this is. uh.
pretty fucked up. Mark.

326
00:22:21.465 --> 00:22:23.717
Why should you be the one
to ask the questions. Mark?

327
00:22:23.718 --> 00:22:25.719
And then how do we know
you're not the killer?

328
00:22:25.720 --> 00:22:27.846
You don't. do you?

329
00:22:27.847 --> 00:22:30.849
I'm sorry but that's not
how this community works.

330
00:22:30.850 --> 00:22:33.727
We do not question each other
at the behest of one person.

331
00:22:33.728 --> 00:22:37.814
Why are you so afraid of a
few little questions. Renee?

332
00:22:37.815 --> 00:22:41.986
Is it because you. with those hands.

333
00:22:43.112 --> 00:22:47.408
just tortured and brutally
slaughtered an innocent man?

334
00:22:51.662 --> 00:22:54.581
I'm not putting myself above you.

335
00:22:54.582 --> 00:22:56.416
but I have experience in these matters.

336
00:22:56.417 --> 00:23:00.170
and my experience tells me that
the only way that we <i>will</i> survive

337
00:23:00.171 --> 00:23:04.758
is by finding this killer
and stopping him. or her.

338
00:23:04.759 --> 00:23:06.802
before they kill again.

339
00:23:09.888 --> 00:23:11.806
And if I refuse?

340
00:23:11.807 --> 00:23:13.350
You have the right to do that...

341
00:23:15.227 --> 00:23:17.813
but I have to say it'll
just make you look guilty.

342
00:23:18.397 --> 00:23:21.232
Oh. seriously? That's where we're
at? We don't follow the herd.

343
00:23:21.233 --> 00:23:23.318
We're just guilty.
You're a fascist. Mark.

344
00:23:23.319 --> 00:23:27.238
If we do this. you have
to participate too.

345
00:23:27.239 --> 00:23:29.282
Oh. you're gonna...? You're
not gonna fight this. Peter?

346
00:23:29.283 --> 00:23:32.077
He's right. You're just
as much of a suspect.

347
00:23:32.078 --> 00:23:33.787
I say we put it to a vote.

348
00:23:33.788 --> 00:23:37.415
No more votes. No more votes!

349
00:23:37.416 --> 00:23:39.209
You don't get to decide for us. Mark.

350
00:23:39.210 --> 00:23:41.295
[HEAVY BREATHS]

351
00:23:47.676 --> 00:23:49.427
All right. This is how it's gonna be.

352
00:23:49.428 --> 00:23:52.597
Dawn will represent our guests.

353
00:23:52.598 --> 00:23:54.224
I'll represent the rest of us.

354
00:23:54.225 --> 00:23:57.435
and when I'm finished questioning
all of you. Dawn can question me.

355
00:23:57.436 --> 00:23:58.312
Fair?

356
00:23:59.313 --> 00:24:02.691
- I can live with that.
- [MARK] Good. It's settled.

357
00:24:04.818 --> 00:24:08.405
I'll go get Dawn. Keira.
let's start with you.

358
00:24:09.448 --> 00:24:10.449
Great.

359
00:24:14.119 --> 00:24:15.995
Where were you when Andi was killed?

360
00:24:15.996 --> 00:24:18.415
- In my room.
- Alone?

361
00:24:18.416 --> 00:24:20.959
Where were <i>you</i>? You were the
last one to see her alive.

362
00:24:26.215 --> 00:24:28.926
Yeah. I was alone. I was reading.

363
00:24:30.969 --> 00:24:34.098
I don't have any
witnesses. just my word.

364
00:24:35.808 --> 00:24:37.184
which I thought meant something.

365
00:24:45.901 --> 00:24:48.278
You used to be an ER nurse
before you came here.

366
00:24:49.530 --> 00:24:50.989
Yes.

367
00:24:50.990 --> 00:24:53.908
So you're familiar with knives
and you're not bothered by gore.

368
00:24:53.909 --> 00:24:54.993
I didn't kill them.

369
00:24:57.496 --> 00:24:58.622
Why did you leave nursing?

370
00:25:05.629 --> 00:25:06.390
Keira?

371
00:25:06.391 --> 00:25:08.715
What does that have
to do with anything?

372
00:25:08.716 --> 00:25:12.261
I don't know yet. but if it was
nothing. you would have told me.

373
00:25:13.470 --> 00:25:17.516
So something important. something
relevant... must have happened.

374
00:25:20.978 --> 00:25:22.604
Keira. you need to answer him.

375
00:25:25.190 --> 00:25:27.192
A patient died on my watch...

376
00:25:29.778 --> 00:25:31.280
because of something I did.

377
00:25:32.614 --> 00:25:33.573
On purpose?

378
00:25:33.574 --> 00:25:35.075
No. not on purpose.

379
00:25:36.243 --> 00:25:37.411
How did he die?

380
00:25:43.459 --> 00:25:44.460
[SIGHS] I...

381
00:25:46.253 --> 00:25:48.005
I was on the floor something like. uh...

382
00:25:50.340 --> 00:25:52.676
[SIGHS] 13 hours. and...

383
00:25:54.595 --> 00:25:56.221
a patient came in and. um...

384
00:25:58.682 --> 00:26:01.602
God. I made a stupid.
stupid mistake. I...

385
00:26:03.562 --> 00:26:07.441
I... I pushed a dose of potassium
instead of dripping it. and...

386
00:26:10.694 --> 00:26:13.780
by the time I realized what I
had done. it was too late.

387
00:26:13.781 --> 00:26:14.823
I...

388
00:26:16.617 --> 00:26:17.618
She was dead.

389
00:26:23.957 --> 00:26:25.584
I wasn't fired or anything. I just...

390
00:26:26.585 --> 00:26:27.586
I...

391
00:26:29.129 --> 00:26:31.381
I couldn't keep doing the
work. you know. I was...

392
00:26:32.299 --> 00:26:33.717
[SIGHS]

393
00:26:35.385 --> 00:26:36.804
I was really lost.

394
00:26:42.184 --> 00:26:43.435
God. then I came here.

395
00:26:49.233 --> 00:26:50.692
Well. I asked you in here first. Keira.

396
00:26:50.693 --> 00:26:53.362
because you have the medical expertise
to pull off these killings.

397
00:26:55.489 --> 00:26:58.449
But what you don't have
that I can see is...

398
00:26:58.450 --> 00:26:59.910
is the motive.

399
00:27:00.869 --> 00:27:02.245
[SOBS]

400
00:27:02.246 --> 00:27:03.288
Can I go?

401
00:27:06.166 --> 00:27:08.585
[SIGHS]

402
00:27:08.586 --> 00:27:09.753
Send the next person in.

403
00:27:11.630 --> 00:27:13.798
I don't know. Maybe if you
guys want to ask me a question

404
00:27:13.799 --> 00:27:18.345
that's not insulting or. uh.
leading. maybe I'll answer you.

405
00:27:21.682 --> 00:27:25.435
You want me to be open-hearted.
share my truth with you.

406
00:27:25.436 --> 00:27:26.478
Okay. I will.

407
00:27:28.146 --> 00:27:29.356
I never liked you.

408
00:27:31.400 --> 00:27:33.360
I didn't from the first time I saw you.

409
00:27:35.904 --> 00:27:38.440
Because I can see through all your shit.

410
00:27:38.441 --> 00:27:40.700
all of your arrogant. entitled...

411
00:27:40.701 --> 00:27:42.035
- Judith.
- Bullshit.

412
00:27:44.121 --> 00:27:44.955
Please sit down.

413
00:27:52.421 --> 00:27:54.172
I think we're all a little on edge.

414
00:27:55.465 --> 00:27:56.466
Yeah.

415
00:28:03.348 --> 00:28:06.393
The presence of these
outsiders really upset you.

416
00:28:08.061 --> 00:28:09.563
Didn't it. Judith?

417
00:28:16.028 --> 00:28:17.613
That doesn't mean I murdered them...

418
00:28:19.656 --> 00:28:21.532
and our friends.

419
00:28:21.533 --> 00:28:23.910
Mark. that's ludicrous.

420
00:28:23.911 --> 00:28:25.037
[DAWN] Is it?

421
00:28:25.621 --> 00:28:27.164
I don't really know anything about you.

422
00:28:28.582 --> 00:28:30.249
Well. you just got here.

423
00:28:30.250 --> 00:28:35.296
Right. and all I know is that you
act like some kind of den mother.

424
00:28:35.297 --> 00:28:40.343
all Zen and calm and one with
the universe. but is that it?

425
00:28:40.344 --> 00:28:42.512
Is that really all there is to you?

426
00:28:47.434 --> 00:28:49.352
This is ridiculous. I won't do this.

427
00:28:49.353 --> 00:28:50.979
No. it's a legitimate question. Judith.

428
00:28:53.065 --> 00:28:54.566
Who were you before you came here?

429
00:28:55.776 --> 00:28:57.110
You know who I am. Mark.

430
00:29:02.324 --> 00:29:03.659
Why do you have clonazepam?

431
00:29:06.245 --> 00:29:07.787
You gave a couple to Renee yesterday

432
00:29:07.788 --> 00:29:09.706
and you can't get that
without a prescription.

433
00:29:10.999 --> 00:29:12.542
I have trouble sleeping.

434
00:29:13.835 --> 00:29:16.452
And I have trouble
believing that someone

435
00:29:16.453 --> 00:29:18.798
prescribed that to you for insomnia.

436
00:29:18.799 --> 00:29:20.466
Come on. Judith. It's
a potent medication.

437
00:29:20.467 --> 00:29:23.637
You don't pop it like aspirin.
So what's the real story?

438
00:29:25.639 --> 00:29:27.349
Dawn may not know you but I do.

439
00:29:29.309 --> 00:29:30.686
And here's what I know about you.

440
00:29:31.895 --> 00:29:33.188
At least what you've told us.

441
00:29:35.315 --> 00:29:36.817
You lost the love of your life.

442
00:29:39.444 --> 00:29:40.487
He left you.

443
00:29:41.738 --> 00:29:43.740
And you... you fell apart.

444
00:29:43.741 --> 00:29:47.369
You had a nervous breakdown. didn't
you? But is that all. Judith?

445
00:29:49.788 --> 00:29:50.956
Is that all?

446
00:29:53.125 --> 00:29:54.876
Did you try and kill yourself?

447
00:29:56.503 --> 00:29:58.046
I know you cut yourself.

448
00:29:58.047 --> 00:29:59.797
- You think it's a secret but we know.
- Shut up!

449
00:29:59.798 --> 00:30:03.009
You are just one crisis away from
negating your entire existence.

450
00:30:03.010 --> 00:30:04.510
- Mark.
- Did their arrival...

451
00:30:04.511 --> 00:30:06.653
Did it finally push you over the edge?

452
00:30:06.654 --> 00:30:08.974
Kill them. kill yourself. kill them all?

453
00:30:11.226 --> 00:30:16.440
I am a much stronger woman now
than I was before I got here.

454
00:30:17.691 --> 00:30:19.901
and you are trying to
use my past against me.

455
00:30:19.902 --> 00:30:22.153
You're gaslighting me. Mark.

456
00:30:22.154 --> 00:30:24.654
This is all your unconscious shit you're

457
00:30:24.655 --> 00:30:26.908
putting on me and I won't take it!

458
00:30:26.909 --> 00:30:29.703
I won't take your shit!

459
00:30:44.468 --> 00:30:45.761
Renee.

460
00:30:48.180 --> 00:30:49.890
These woods are like your
backyard. aren't they?

461
00:30:53.018 --> 00:30:56.355
And the chainsaw. and the auger.
you're very familiar with those.

462
00:30:57.647 --> 00:30:59.358
So are half the people in this house.

463
00:31:03.111 --> 00:31:04.529
Why would I kill Antoine?

464
00:31:08.200 --> 00:31:09.201
For the money.

465
00:31:12.537 --> 00:31:13.538
What money?

466
00:31:15.290 --> 00:31:16.457
Well. as your legal husband.

467
00:31:16.458 --> 00:31:20.002
Antoine was entitled to half of
the profits from the land sale.

468
00:31:20.003 --> 00:31:23.214
even if your marriage
was never consummated.

469
00:31:23.215 --> 00:31:24.674
You don't know shit about us!

470
00:31:26.134 --> 00:31:27.596
Okay. our marriage may not have been

471
00:31:27.597 --> 00:31:29.179
conventional but we loved each other!

472
00:31:31.640 --> 00:31:33.350
I would have died for him.

473
00:31:37.270 --> 00:31:39.731
And you killed for him.
Let's not forget that.

474
00:32:06.425 --> 00:32:07.426
"Dear J...

475
00:32:09.428 --> 00:32:11.721
I lost my temper with you earlier today.

476
00:32:12.973 --> 00:32:16.075
My only excuse is that I'm trying so

477
00:32:16.076 --> 00:32:19.562
hard to remain strong and to be brave.

478
00:32:19.563 --> 00:32:22.858
and I'm not allowing
myself to feel fear.

479
00:32:24.401 --> 00:32:25.902
So I took it out on you.

480
00:32:29.281 --> 00:32:30.365
Please forgive me.

481
00:32:32.784 --> 00:32:33.785
Your Wren."

482
00:32:47.757 --> 00:32:48.842
Is it my turn now?

483
00:32:55.390 --> 00:32:56.516
Tell me about that girl.

484
00:32:57.726 --> 00:32:59.269
The one that you worked with.

485
00:33:02.772 --> 00:33:04.065
That was an accident.

486
00:33:08.653 --> 00:33:11.948
And why did you come back
here? Please don't lie.

487
00:33:15.285 --> 00:33:18.872
To... to find her body and remove it...

488
00:33:20.332 --> 00:33:22.667
before they start building that resort.

489
00:33:22.668 --> 00:33:24.252
And whose idea was that?

490
00:33:29.132 --> 00:33:30.133
It was mine.

491
00:33:34.346 --> 00:33:40.059
Talvinder was not this sweet
innocent little victim. okay?

492
00:33:40.060 --> 00:33:43.187
She was cruel. and manipulative.
and she didn't care who she hurt.

493
00:33:43.188 --> 00:33:46.440
- So she deserved to die?
- No. that's not what I'm saying.

494
00:33:46.441 --> 00:33:47.525
Well. that's what I'm hearing.

495
00:33:47.526 --> 00:33:50.736
You killed her and you hid
her body God knows where.

496
00:33:50.737 --> 00:33:52.154
You're not hearing. It was an accident.

497
00:33:52.155 --> 00:33:54.448
- Oh. yes. it was an accident.
- Yes.

498
00:33:54.449 --> 00:33:57.160
That you've been covering
up for five years.

499
00:33:58.161 --> 00:34:01.789
What is this? What are you
doing? Why are you doing this?

500
00:34:01.790 --> 00:34:05.501
You say that Talvinder was
cruel and manipulative.

501
00:34:05.502 --> 00:34:08.045
- She was.
- Was she so cruel and so manipulative

502
00:34:08.046 --> 00:34:10.965
that she forced you to
throw her off a cliff.

503
00:34:10.966 --> 00:34:13.217
or drown her in a lake. or
shoot her through the head

504
00:34:13.218 --> 00:34:14.719
- with an arrow by accident?!
- Fuck you!

505
00:34:14.720 --> 00:34:16.762
- Fuck off. Mark!
- How do I know?!

506
00:34:16.763 --> 00:34:19.015
How do I know that it wasn't you

507
00:34:19.016 --> 00:34:22.393
who killed your friends and
my friends to cover this up?

508
00:34:22.394 --> 00:34:25.814
Who invited everyone up and sabotaged
your car. and brought a gun?!

509
00:34:28.608 --> 00:34:29.609
How do I know?

510
00:34:40.620 --> 00:34:42.330
Peter. it's your turn.

511
00:34:42.331 --> 00:34:44.332
No. no. no. Fuck this. okay?

512
00:34:44.333 --> 00:34:48.377
All you've done is get
everyone more upset.

513
00:34:48.378 --> 00:34:51.213
- And you've gotten nowhere.
- [JUDITH] He's right. Mark.

514
00:34:51.214 --> 00:34:52.604
You're destroying what little we have

515
00:34:52.605 --> 00:34:54.175
left of this community. acting this way.

516
00:34:54.176 --> 00:34:58.596
Someone in this room is killing us.

517
00:34:58.597 --> 00:35:01.141
They're hunting us down one by one!

518
00:35:03.310 --> 00:35:07.146
This is on you. You and Antoine.

519
00:35:07.147 --> 00:35:09.148
Excuse me?

520
00:35:09.149 --> 00:35:11.025
I came here to find
peace and I found it.

521
00:35:11.026 --> 00:35:13.054
I did. but then you let them in and

522
00:35:13.055 --> 00:35:15.196
everything. everything's unraveled.

523
00:35:15.197 --> 00:35:17.490
People are being murdered.

524
00:35:17.491 --> 00:35:21.410
Girls are buried in caves and this
community is turning on itself.

525
00:35:21.411 --> 00:35:23.079
and that's on you.

526
00:35:23.080 --> 00:35:24.205
Judith.

527
00:35:25.081 --> 00:35:26.540
Yeah. we're done.

528
00:35:26.541 --> 00:35:28.501
- Are you afraid of questions. Peter?
- Whatever. man.

529
00:35:28.502 --> 00:35:29.586
[DAWN] Mark.

530
00:35:31.087 --> 00:35:33.589
We're done when I say we're done.

531
00:35:33.590 --> 00:35:35.383
- Why don't you put the gun down?
- [DAWN] Mark.

532
00:35:35.384 --> 00:35:39.053
When I have decided who the killer is!

533
00:35:39.054 --> 00:35:40.471
Mark.

534
00:35:40.472 --> 00:35:42.557
- Give me the gun.
- When I decide!

535
00:35:44.017 --> 00:35:48.771
Now you. get in that room and you
answer my fucking questions!

536
00:35:48.772 --> 00:35:50.065
[GRUNTING. GURGLING]

537
00:35:58.406 --> 00:36:00.783
Mark. he's choking to death. Please!

538
00:36:00.784 --> 00:36:02.535
[NOAH WHEEZING. LABORED BREATHING]

539
00:36:04.788 --> 00:36:05.955
Our friend is dying.

540
00:36:07.165 --> 00:36:09.000
So either you shoot me...

541
00:36:10.001 --> 00:36:12.045
or get that gun out of my face.

542
00:36:23.306 --> 00:36:25.349
[KEIRA PANTING]

543
00:36:25.350 --> 00:36:28.018
It's okay. it's okay. it's okay.

544
00:36:28.019 --> 00:36:29.729
Stay. stay. stay. Come on.

545
00:36:37.946 --> 00:36:39.698
[SOBBING]

546
00:36:54.337 --> 00:36:55.588
[SOBS]

547
00:36:58.550 --> 00:36:59.551
I'm sorry.

548
00:37:01.511 --> 00:37:03.388
[SOBBING]

549
00:37:25.785 --> 00:37:27.287
[DOOR OPENS]

550
00:37:32.709 --> 00:37:33.710
Gun.

551
00:37:35.712 --> 00:37:37.130
- Dawn.
- Gun.

552
00:37:38.465 --> 00:37:40.633
Dawn. that wasn't me in there.

553
00:37:40.634 --> 00:37:43.553
No? What was it. then. your evil twin?

554
00:37:45.805 --> 00:37:47.891
That's fair enough. It was me.

555
00:37:48.975 --> 00:37:51.352
It was. is me. a part of me...

556
00:37:52.812 --> 00:37:55.315
that I've been trying to deny for years.

557
00:37:58.193 --> 00:38:00.945
A part of me that I thought
was gone for good.

558
00:38:06.868 --> 00:38:08.828
I thought I'd found
peace here. you know.

559
00:38:10.663 --> 00:38:12.207
I thought I knew who I was.

560
00:38:14.793 --> 00:38:16.503
I thought I could trust my own goodness.

561
00:38:19.172 --> 00:38:21.841
That was all just a lie.

562
00:38:21.842 --> 00:38:23.384
I don't know what you're talking about.

563
00:38:27.096 --> 00:38:29.557
I used to be a guy who
handled things. you know.

564
00:38:30.975 --> 00:38:32.310
I wasn't afraid of anything.

565
00:38:33.728 --> 00:38:34.729
Nothing scared me.

566
00:38:38.566 --> 00:38:39.567
Until one day...

567
00:38:40.860 --> 00:38:44.906
when I got shot because of
something that I'd done...

568
00:38:46.783 --> 00:38:48.701
along with a woman that I cared about.

569
00:38:50.662 --> 00:38:52.372
You see. there's another lie.

570
00:38:55.708 --> 00:38:56.793
I didn't care about her.

571
00:38:57.877 --> 00:39:00.588
I was just using her. Fucking her.

572
00:39:03.925 --> 00:39:05.009
We were at a restaurant.

573
00:39:06.094 --> 00:39:09.472
And he shot her through
the back of the head.

574
00:39:10.849 --> 00:39:15.895
And I had her blood and bits
of brain and her skull...

575
00:39:17.063 --> 00:39:18.064
in my mouth.

576
00:39:25.071 --> 00:39:27.282
She just died like that
right in front of me.

577
00:39:29.868 --> 00:39:31.160
And all I could think was...

578
00:39:32.871 --> 00:39:34.539
thank God that wasn't me.

579
00:39:39.669 --> 00:39:42.504
I would do anything to save myself.

580
00:39:42.505 --> 00:39:47.719
I would lie. I would cheat.
steal. kill. destroy.

581
00:39:49.304 --> 00:39:53.141
I would let an innocent
girl die instead of me.

582
00:39:55.351 --> 00:39:57.520
And I thought I buried
that guy out here.

583
00:39:59.314 --> 00:40:02.191
And today he just came right
back out of the grave.

584
00:40:09.741 --> 00:40:10.742
Hey.

585
00:40:12.744 --> 00:40:14.329
That's why I need my gun back.

586
00:40:16.205 --> 00:40:18.374
'Cause I don't know what
that guy is capable of.

587
00:40:22.128 --> 00:40:23.952
Yeah. but we do know what you and your

588
00:40:23.953 --> 00:40:25.673
friends are capable of. don't we?

589
00:40:25.674 --> 00:40:27.424
No.

590
00:40:27.425 --> 00:40:29.177
Until help comes. I keep the gun.

591
00:40:35.975 --> 00:40:38.102
[DOOR OPENS]

592
00:40:38.103 --> 00:40:39.019
[SIGHS]

593
00:40:39.020 --> 00:40:41.307
I suppose you're
here for your apology.

594
00:40:41.308 --> 00:40:42.857
You crossed so many lines.

595
00:40:44.776 --> 00:40:47.153
We'll debrief some other time.
Right now. I need your help.

596
00:40:48.196 --> 00:40:49.947
With what?

597
00:40:49.948 --> 00:40:50.990
Bring the gun.

598
00:40:55.244 --> 00:40:57.538
What the hell are we doing here?

599
00:40:57.539 --> 00:41:00.958
- Renee. answer me!
- I need to check something!

600
00:41:00.959 --> 00:41:02.126
That is not an answer.

601
00:41:03.294 --> 00:41:05.295
- You tell me or I'm heading back.
- It could be nothing.

602
00:41:05.296 --> 00:41:06.630
It probably is nothing.

603
00:41:06.631 --> 00:41:07.715
What?

604
00:41:08.675 --> 00:41:11.802
Someone. and I'm not saying who.

605
00:41:11.803 --> 00:41:12.850
said something they shouldn't have said.

606
00:41:12.851 --> 00:41:13.805
something they shouldn't have known.

607
00:41:16.057 --> 00:41:17.391
About what?

608
00:41:17.392 --> 00:41:18.434
The past.

609
00:41:19.644 --> 00:41:21.145
When this place was a summer camp.

610
00:41:23.439 --> 00:41:26.442
Look. after Glen. I... I just
needed to be sure. okay?

611
00:41:26.443 --> 00:41:28.403
I just need you to stand guard.

612
00:41:51.217 --> 00:41:53.094
[COUGHS]

613
00:42:09.902 --> 00:42:11.320
[RUSTLING]

614
00:42:31.174 --> 00:42:32.550
[SIGHS]

615
00:42:48.232 --> 00:42:51.652
And we're a vegan community.
or we're trying to be.

616
00:42:51.653 --> 00:42:55.405
I'll admit it. I occasionally
fall off the wagon.

617
00:42:55.406 --> 00:42:56.574
Just can't quit a good burger.

618
00:42:58.242 --> 00:43:01.161
And this is Judith. our den
mother. Judith. this is Mark.

619
00:43:01.162 --> 00:43:02.204
Mark Rankin.

620
00:43:02.205 --> 00:43:03.789
Oh.

621
00:43:03.790 --> 00:43:05.582
I'm a hugger.

622
00:43:05.583 --> 00:43:07.043
I hope that's okay.

623
00:43:07.835 --> 00:43:10.880
- That's fine with me.
- Mmm. Welcome. Mark.

624
00:43:12.632 --> 00:43:15.134
Thank you. Thank you all.

625
00:43:17.637 --> 00:43:19.721
I feel really good being here.

626
00:43:19.722 --> 00:43:21.682
There's something special about
this place. isn't there?

627
00:43:23.101 --> 00:43:24.685
I've been searching for something.

628
00:43:26.187 --> 00:43:28.689
[SIGHS] A sense of safety and...

629
00:43:28.690 --> 00:43:30.066
I think I've found it.

630
00:43:31.984 --> 00:43:32.985
And that touches me.

631
00:43:34.487 --> 00:43:35.988
This home is for all of us.

632
00:43:38.866 --> 00:43:40.159
It's okay. Mark.

633
00:43:41.619 --> 00:43:44.913
It's okay to let down. Feel it.

634
00:43:44.914 --> 00:43:46.249
We can hold it with you.

635
00:43:49.710 --> 00:43:51.671
- Thank you. Thank you.
- Thank you.

636
00:44:02.181 --> 00:44:05.268
[MOTOR DRONING]

637
00:44:45.725 --> 00:44:48.186
[MAN] <i>Hey. Andi. Welcome
back to Camp Motega.</i>

638
00:44:50.062 --> 00:44:51.625
Um. stand in front of our photographer

639
00:44:51.626 --> 00:44:53.106
here. We're gonna take a picture.

640
00:44:53.107 --> 00:44:54.316
Mm-hmm.

641
00:44:54.317 --> 00:44:56.818
Uh. let's do one where you smile
for the camera. yeah? Say cheese.

642
00:44:56.819 --> 00:44:58.779
Yeah. sure. Cheese.

643
00:44:58.780 --> 00:44:59.864
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

644
00:45:05.161 --> 00:45:07.329
Okay. we're taking another photo
'cause I look like Jabba the Hutt.

645
00:45:07.330 --> 00:45:08.747
except with more chins.

646
00:45:08.748 --> 00:45:09.790
Okay.

647
00:45:10.833 --> 00:45:12.168
Just one more.

648
00:45:14.795 --> 00:45:17.423
[MAN] Please stand a bit
to your right. Awesome.

649
00:45:19.050 --> 00:45:20.968
I think it would look better
if you gave us a smile.

650
00:45:20.969 --> 00:45:23.470
Can you give us a big smile. please?

651
00:45:23.471 --> 00:45:24.513
Sure.

652
00:45:25.431 --> 00:45:26.807
[CAMERA BEEPS. SHUTTER CLICKS]

653
00:45:30.478 --> 00:45:31.687
[MAN] <i>You know the drill. right?</i>

654
00:45:31.688 --> 00:45:34.940
I never take a picture I don't
like. so do what you gotta do.

655
00:45:34.941 --> 00:45:36.692
[CAMERA BEEPS. SHUTTER CLICKS]

656
00:45:38.903 --> 00:45:39.737
[MAN] <i>Say cheese.</i>

657
00:45:40.738 --> 00:45:41.655
Say cheese.

658
00:45:41.656 --> 00:45:44.074
How's it going? "Gouda." No?

659
00:45:44.075 --> 00:45:45.283
You gotta "brie" kidding me.

660
00:45:45.284 --> 00:45:47.244
[CHUCKLES] That was funny.

661
00:45:50.748 --> 00:45:53.000
[MAN] Susan. photo time.

662
00:45:54.251 --> 00:45:56.461
- Okay. say cheese.
- Fromage.

663
00:45:56.462 --> 00:45:57.797
[CAMERA BEEPS. SHUTTER CLICKS]

664
00:46:05.262 --> 00:46:06.555
Jesus.

665
00:46:07.223 --> 00:46:09.182
[MAN] Everyone's gotta have a
picture taken. camp rules.

666
00:46:09.183 --> 00:46:10.308
[WREN] Fuck your rules.

667
00:46:10.309 --> 00:46:12.561
[MAN] You want to spend the summer
working the grounds or not?

668
00:46:12.562 --> 00:46:13.478
[WREN] Yeah.

669
00:46:13.479 --> 00:46:15.043
[MAN] Then please step in front of the

670
00:46:15.044 --> 00:46:16.565
camera and let us take your picture.

671
00:46:24.615 --> 00:46:26.241
Renee!

672
00:46:26.242 --> 00:46:29.244
- [SNOWMOBILE REVVING]
- Hey! Hey!

673
00:46:29.245 --> 00:46:32.330
Follow my voice! We need your help!

674
00:46:32.331 --> 00:46:33.708
Hey!

675
00:46:36.502 --> 00:46:37.586
Over here!

676
00:46:37.587 --> 00:46:39.087
Oh. no. no. no.

677
00:46:39.088 --> 00:46:42.174
It's okay. It's okay. We need your...

678
00:46:46.554 --> 00:46:47.930
[ENGINE REVVING]

679
00:46:56.188 --> 00:46:57.273
[DOOR OPENS]

680
00:47:04.905 --> 00:47:06.407
[PANTING]

681
00:47:15.374 --> 00:47:17.043
[ENGINE STARTS AND REVS]

682
00:47:19.336 --> 00:47:20.379
[GRUNTS]

683
00:47:21.881 --> 00:47:24.467
[SNOWMOBILE REVVING]

684
00:47:33.476 --> 00:47:34.977
[GRUNTING]

685
00:47:38.397 --> 00:47:39.982
[WHEEZING]

686
00:47:57.792 --> 00:47:58.834
[ENGINE REVVING]

687
00:47:59.752 --> 00:48:02.295
- [IMPACT THUD]
- [RENEE SCREAMS]

